  "text": "We observed that the correlation fit between the simulated and empirical F ST values are high ( Figure 5A ), but notably less than the correlation between the simulated and empirical p values ( Figure 5B ). We believe that this is due to the fact that we used demographic parameters for two populations (East Asian and African populations [CITATION_1] for the F ST simulations, while assumed parameters for only the East Asian populations for the p calculations.",
